tor for apria healthcare services mike also serves on the board of directors of boeing and stericyclepreviously in a year corporate career he served  years as presidentceocoo at nortel motorola and five ge businesses in the high tech industrial consumer and financial services industries demonstrated ability to develop strategy simplify complexity attract and develop strong teams and drive execution in the  years of pl responsibility revenue growth exceeded  per year and ebitda gains averaged  bps per year among his philanthropic activities he is vice chairman and leads the strategy committee for ausl the organization that helps turnaround the most challenged public schools in chicago he is a visiting lecturer at the northwestern kellogg school of management and duke university’s fuqua school of business he is a founding director and chairman of macedonia  an organization dedicated to enhancing the country’s economic and democracy development he and his wife robin are cochairs and past national chairs for duke universitys parents committee mike robin and their three sons matt kirk and todd are officers of the zafirovski family foundation formed in  focusing on education and health issues zafirovski holds a ba in mathematics from edinboro university in pennsylvania where he captained the intercollegiate soccer and swimming teams in  edinboro university awarded him an honorary doctorate degree a native of macedonia he received the ellis island medal of honor in  and the distinguished leadership award from the ny hall of science in experiencefounder president ceothe zaf group – present  yearsexecutive advisorthe blackstone group – present  yearsmember of board of directorsboeing – present  yearsnon executive chairmandjo global  a blackstone company – present  yearsnonexecutive chairmanpolymer group inc a blackstone company – present  yearsmember of board of directorsstericycle – present  yearsmember of board of directorsapria healthcare a blackstone company – present  y